			<div class="gud-style__intro">
				<h1>A guide to digital design at the Guardian</h1>
				<h1 class="gud-style__date">26/07/18</h1>
			</div>
		</div>
		<a class="gud-style__cta" href="#colour-palette-4">
			<h2></h2>
		</a>
	</div>
	<main>
		<section id="cards-containers" data-section-name="cards-containers">
			<div class="slide" id="cards-containers-1">
				<div class="text">
					<div class="paragraph">
						<span class="title">Introduction</span>
						The Guardian website is made up of a series of fronts and articles.
					</div>
				</div>
				<div
					style="background-color:#E7E7E7"
					class="image"
					data-section-number="1 / 8"
					data-section-title="Introduction"
				>
					<div class="image__inner">
						<img src="https://uploads.guim.co.uk/2018/02/09/Wide_No_Grid.png" />
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
			<div class="slide" id="cards-containers-2">
				<div class="text">
					<div class="paragraph">
						<span class="title">Introduction</span>
						Fronts are made up of containers — these allow stories to be grouped in a logical manner,
						by theme or subject matter.
					</div>
				</div>
				<div
					style="background-color:#E7E7E7"
					class="image"
					data-section-number="2 / 8"
					data-section-title="Introduction"
				>
					<div class="image__inner">
						<img src="https://uploads.guim.co.uk/2018/02/07/culture_wire.png" />
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
			<div class="slide" id="cards-containers-3">
				<div class="text">
					<div class="paragraph">
						<span class="title">Introduction</span>
						Containers are composed of modular story cards. These are designed to be flexible; they expand
						and contract depending on the number of stories added to them.
					</div>
				</div>
				<div
					style="background-color:#E7E7E7"
					class="image"
					data-section-number="3 / 8"
					data-section-title="Introduction"
				>
					<div class="image__inner">
						<img src="https://uploads.guim.co.uk/2018/02/07/culture_full.png" />
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
			<div class="slide" id="cards-containers-4">
				<div class="text">
					<div class="paragraph">
						<span class="title">Introduction</span>
						Cards can display an image, kicker, headline, standfirst and meta information.

						<ul class="item-list">
							<li>Kicker — Guardian Headline Bold</li>
							<li>Headline — Guardian Headline Medium</li>
							<li>Standfirst — Guardian Text Egyptian</li>
							<li>Meta — Guardian Text Sans</li>
						</ul>
					</div>
				</div>
				<div
					style="background-color:#E7E7E7"
					class="image"
					data-section-number="4 / 8"
					data-section-title="Introduction"
				>
					<div class="image__inner">
						<img src="https://uploads.guim.co.uk/2018/02/13/labelled_cards.png" />
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
			<div class="slide" id="cards-containers-5">
				<div class="text">
					<div class="paragraph">
						<span class="title">Introduction</span>
						We have a variety of different card sizes which create hierarchy and pace on the page, and
						allow the reader to quickly gauge a story’s importance.
					</div>
				</div>
				<div
					style="background-color:#E7E7E7"
					class="image"
					data-section-number="5 / 8"
					data-section-title="Introduction"
				>
					<div class="image__inner">
						<img src="https://uploads.guim.co.uk/2018/02/20/card_sizes.jpg" />
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
			<div class="slide" id="cards-containers-6">
				<div class="text">
					<div class="paragraph">
						<span class="title">Introduction</span>
						This is a selection of the card types. Each card type is designed to impart the tone of the
						story.
					</div>
				</div>
				<div
					style="background-color:#E7E7E7"
					class="image"
					data-section-number="6 / 8"
					data-section-title="Introduction"
				>
					<div class="image__inner">
						<img src="https://uploads.guim.co.uk/2018/02/13/cards_grid_labelled.png" />
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
			<div class="slide" id="cards-containers-7">
				<div class="text">
					<div class="paragraph">
						<span class="title">Introduction</span>
						Below is a selection of the article types. Articles follow the design language of the cards,
						with each having its own distinct flavour and tone.
					</div>
				</div>
				<div
					style="background-color:#E7E7E7"
					class="image"
					data-section-number="7 / 8"
					data-section-title="Introduction"
				>
					<div class="image__inner">
						<img src="https://uploads.guim.co.uk/2018/02/20/articles_updated.jpg" />
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
			<div class="slide" id="cards-containers-8">
				<div class="text">
					<div class="paragraph">
						<span class="title">Introduction</span>
						Thrashers are custom-designed containers usually promoting a single article or series.
					</div>
				</div>
				<div
					style="background-color:#E7E7E7"
					class="image"
					data-section-number="8 / 8"
					data-section-title="Introduction"
				>
					<div class="image__inner">
						<img src="https://uploads.guim.co.uk/2018/02/07/thrasher.png" />
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>
		<section id="grids-spacing" data-section-name="grids-spacing">
			<div class="slide" id="grids-spacing-1">
				<div class="text">
					<div class="paragraph">
						<span class="title">Grids &amp;spacing</span>
						The grid provides the substrate and unifies how we arrange information on all of our digital
						platforms.
					</div>
				</div>
				<div
					style="background-color:#ffe500"
					class="image"
					data-section-number="1 / 7"
					data-section-title="Grids &amp; spacing"
				>
					<div class="image__inner">
						<img src="https://uploads.guim.co.uk/2018/02/12/chaos_big.svg" />
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
			<div class="slide" id="grids-spacing-2">
				<div class="text">
					<div class="paragraph">
						<span class="title">Grids &amp;spacing</span>
						The desktop grid is based on columns of 60px with 20px gutters.
					</div>
				</div>
				<div
					style="background-color:#E7E7E7"
					class="image"
					data-section-number="2 / 7"
					data-section-title="Grids &amp; spacing"
				>
					<div class="image__inner">
						<img src="https://uploads.guim.co.uk/2018/02/07/Wide_grid_on.png" />
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
			<div class="slide" id="grids-spacing-3">
				<div class="text">
					<div class="paragraph">
						<span class="title">Grids &amp;spacing</span>
						We use four fixed grid sizes on large screens:

						<ul class="item-list">
							<li>Wide — 1300px</li>
							<li>LeftCol — 1140px</li>
							<li>Desktop — 980px</li>
							<li>Tablet — 740px</li>
						</ul>
					</div>
				</div>
				<div
					style="background-color:#E7E7E7"
					class="image"
					data-section-number="3 / 7"
					data-section-title="Grids &amp; spacing"
				>
					<div class="image__inner">
						<img src="https://uploads.guim.co.uk/2018/02/20/grid_animation.gif" />
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
			<div class="slide" id="grids-spacing-4">
				<div class="text">
					<div class="paragraph">
						<span class="title">Grids &amp;spacing</span>
						We use a fluid grid on mobile devices, with tweak points at:

						<ul class="item-list">
							<li>Phablet — 740px</li>
							<li>MobileLandscape — 480px</li>
							<li>MobileMedium — 375px</li>
						</ul>
					</div>
				</div>
				<div
					style="background-color:#E7E7E7"
					class="image"
					data-section-number="4 / 7"
					data-section-title="Grids &amp; spacing"
				>
					<div class="image__inner">
						<img src="https://uploads.guim.co.uk/2018/02/08/mobile_grid.png" />
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
			<div class="slide" id="grids-spacing-5">
				<div class="text">
					<div class="paragraph">
						<span class="title">Grids &amp;spacing</span>
						Spacing is intentionally used to echo the placement of the typography in print.
					</div>
				</div>
				<div
					style="background-color:#E7E7E7"
					class="image"
					data-section-number="5 / 7"
					data-section-title="Grids &amp; spacing"
				>
					<div class="image__inner">
						<img src="https://uploads.guim.co.uk/2018/02/13/paper_full.png" />
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
			<div class="slide" id="grids-spacing-6">
				<div class="text">
					<div class="paragraph">
						<span class="title">Grids &amp;spacing</span>
						Rules govern the placement of display and text elements and maintain consistency across print
						and digital platforms.
					</div>
				</div>
				<div
					style="background-color:#E7E7E7"
					class="image"
					data-section-number="6 / 7"
					data-section-title="Grids &amp; spacing"
				>
					<div class="image__inner">
						<img src="https://uploads.guim.co.uk/2018/02/13/paper_lableled.png" />
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
			<div class="slide" id="grids-spacing-7">
				<div class="text">
					<div class="paragraph">
						<span class="title">Grids &amp;spacing</span>
						This alignment is consistent on headlines, bylines and container titles across fronts and
						articles.
					</div>
				</div>
				<div
					style="background-color:#E7E7E7"
					class="image"
					data-section-number="7 / 7"
					data-section-title="Grids &amp; spacing"
				>
					<div class="image__inner">
						<img src="https://uploads.guim.co.uk/2018/02/09/card_spacing_labelled_colour.png" />
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>
		<section id="brand-use" data-section-name="brand-use">
			<div class="slide" id="brand-use-1">
				<div class="text">
					<div class="paragraph">
						<span class="title">Brand use</span>
						The Guardian has two expressions of its brand.
					</div>
				</div>
				<div class="image" data-section-number="1 / 3" data-section-title="Brand use">
					<div class="image__inner">
						<img src="https://uploads.guim.co.uk/2018/02/08/logo.png" />
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
			<div class="slide" id="brand-use-2">
				<div class="text">
					<div class="paragraph">
						<span class="title">Brand use</span>
						The logo and the roundel are always aligned either top right or bottom right.
					</div>
				</div>
				<div
					style="background-color:#E7E7E7"
					class="image"
					data-section-number="2 / 3"
					data-section-title="Brand use"
				>
					<div class="image__inner">
						<img src="https://uploads.guim.co.uk/2018/02/08/logo_placement.gif" />
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
			<div class="slide" id="brand-use-3">
				<div class="text">
					<div class="paragraph">
						<span class="title">Brand use</span>
						The roundel acts as a simplified expression of the brand — often used to indicate Guardian
						content on- and off-platform.

